ocrad: ocrad (GNU OCR program and library)
ocrad:
ocrad: GNU Ocrad is an OCR (Optical Character Recognition) program and
ocrad: library based on a feature extraction method. It reads images
ocrad: in png or pnm formats and produces text in byte (8-bit) or UTF-8
ocrad: formats. The formats pbm (bitmap), pgm (greyscale), and ppm (color)
ocrad: are collectively known as pnm.  Ocrad includes a layout analyser
ocrad: able to separate the columns and blocks of text normally found
ocrad: on printed pages.  Ocrad can be used as a stand-alone console
ocrad: application, or as a backend to other programs.
ocrad: Home: https://www.gnu.org/software/ocrad/
